This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the generalization properties of neural networks. Additionally, it also involves the use of an evolutionary algorithm, which falls under the scope of optimization techniques used in machine learning. 

The paper also involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and perturbations in input images, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the role of optimization techniques in generalization robustness, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper proposes a cost function inspired by literature in domain adaptation, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
